<TITLE> Delwar guarded in his reaction </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 9 (bdnews24.com)  Acting BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain Sunday said how much the government relaxes the restrictions on indoor politics needed to be seen. "There is nothing called indoor politics in the constitution. We want politics to be open. The sooner the government does it the better it is for democracy and election," Delwar said in a guarded reaction in the evening. "Hope is there after the lifting of the restrictions. Now it's to be seen how much the government relaxes them." bdnew
